Title: Encyclopedia of Science Projects
Author: প্যাম রবসন
Summary:
Every project in this ENCYCLOPEDIA is interesting to do and intriguing to watch. Each uses readily available, everyday materials and includes detailed instructions and diagrams to ensure your success, as well as helpful suggestions for exhibition. Whether you want to discover how things work or investigate about Air, Water, Electricity, Magnetism, Sound, Light and many more, you will find a surefire science-fair winner to satisfy your curiosity.

Be sure to follow the instructions carefully while performing a project under the supervision of an adult.
